<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-289] The NIO transport must handle the sudden and un-expected closure of keep-alive connections by external systems which may be under load</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-289</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the NIO transport deals with external servers (such as JBoss), it defaults to using keep-alive connections. However, when an external system is under load, they have the freedom to abruptly close such keep-alive connections to ensure correct operation. The NIO transport needs to expect and handle this situation gracefully&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;More information can be found from the thread &lt;a href=&quot;http://markmail.org/message/dv4v7oypr7oa4rqx&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://markmail.org/message/dv4v7oypr7oa4rqx&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Both on Windows and Linux, When talking to an external JBoss 4.2.2 server under load</environment>
